{
  "stem": "22869.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had-- a lot of us guys who-- you know, once you came back a little bit to strength, you also came back a little bit to your faith.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we used to-- when Rosh Hashanah came in 1944, we decided a bunch of us were going to make a-- a quorum, a minyan, which it's called in-- in Hebrew, and we'll conduct services.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when I was a child, I used to sing in a choir by a cantor, for which I used to get paid for.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remembered a lot of the liturgy by heart.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- and we had-- we had the prayer books anyway, so we organized that-- that-- that-- I don't remember how many guys were there, but 20 or 30.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We got a hold of a few of these prayer shawls, and we put them on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course we put on guards in all the corners of the barracks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was conducting services there on Rosh Hashanah, 1944.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were a lot of guys who was really mocking us because when the-- we used to say in the evening, the big fires from the crematoria-- most of the people who-- who even were believers at home lost their faith in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Used to come to the guys like myself who-- who-- I mean, there was nothing left in me as far as faith is, that I still said I believe in God.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I hope that one day I'll be out of here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But further than that, there was no such thing as keeping Saturday or watching for kosher.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was far, far away from your mind, because you were so happy to be alive.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
